program usage: [options] <filename>.bmp

options:

	-h, --help                         print this useful hint
	
	--rectangle [options] <filename>.bmp
	
		-s, --start x,y                set the upper left corner of rectangle
		
		-e, --end x,y                  set the right bottom corner of rectangle 
		
		-w, --width pixels             (optional) the line width (1 by default) 
		
		-c, --color color              color of lines in hex format; color from [#000000; #FFFFFF]
		                               example: --color "#FF00FF" (note: use "" to get correct input)
		
		-f, --fill color               (optional) fill color in hex format; color from [#000000; #FFFFFF]
                                        example: --fill "#FF00FF" (note: use "" to get correct input)

		-n, --new <new_filename>.bmp   (optional) if option called then new file will be created instead of rewriting 
		
		
	--circle [options] <filename>.bmp 
	
	Warning: circle can be specified only with rectangle or with point and radius 
	[i.e. -s and -e or -p and -r can be used at time]
	
		-s, --start x,y                upper left corner of the rectangle into which the circle will be inscribed
		
		-e, --end x,y                  the right bottom corner of rectangle into which the circle will be inscribed
		
		-p, --point x,y                coordinates of center dot
		
		-r, --radius r                 radius of circle
		
		-w, --width pixels             (optional) specifies the line width (1 by default) 
		
		-c, --color color              color of lines in hex format; color from [#000000; #FFFFFF]
        		                       example: --color "#FF00FF" (note: use "" to get correct input)

        -f, --fill color               (optional) fill color in hex format; color from [#000000; #FFFFFF]
                                        example: --fill "#FF00FF" (note: use "" to get correct input)

		-n, --new <new_filename>.bmp   (optional) if option called then new file will be created instead of rewriting 
			
	
	--rotate [options] <filename>.bmp 
	
		-d, --direction dir            (optional) direction to rotate can be 'left' or 'right' (default is left)
		
		-a, --angle angle              rotating angle can be 90 or 180 or 270 degrees
		
		-s, --start x,y                set the upper left corner of area
		
		-e, --end x,y                  set the right bottom corner of area
		
		-n, --new <new_filename>.bmp   (optional) if option called then new file will be created instead of rewriting 
		
		
	--frame [options] <filename>.bmp
		-t, --type type                specifies frame type (now supported 0 types)
		
		-c, --color color              color of lines in hex format; color from [#000000; #FFFFFF]
                		               example: --color "#FF00FF" (note: use "" to get correct input)
		
		-w, --width pixels             (optional)? specifies the frame width <insert num by default>
		
		-n, --new <new_filename>.bmp   (optional) if option called then new file will be created instead of rewriting
